        <h3 id="admin-lookups-endpoints" class="h5 mt-5">Admin lookups endpoints</h3>

        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <p class="mb-0"><strong>Read-only admin config catalog.</strong> These endpoints require the <code>AdminLookups</code> permission scope with <code>read</code> access. Use them to discover the kinds of admin configuration COMPASS exposes (business areas, RAID statuses, priorities, RAG definitions, etc.) and fetch the values for each.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- List Admin Lookups -->
        <div class="api-endpoint">
            <div class="api-endpoint-header">
                <span class="api-method api-method-get">GET</span>
                <span class="api-path">/api/v1/admin/lookups</span>
                <span class="ml-auto"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
            </div>
            <div class="api-endpoint-body">
                <p>List every admin lookup type at a glance. Use the <code>key</code> field to drive a follow-up call to <code>/api/v1/admin/lookups/{key}</code>.</p>

                <h5 class="mt-3"><span class="api-response-code api-response-200">200 OK</span></h5>
                <div class="api-code-block">
                    <pre>{
  "totalRecords": 38,
  "data": [
    {
      "key": "business-areas",
      "label": "Business areas",
      "category": "core",
      "description": "Business areas used to classify work items and map to divisions.",
      "itemCount": 12,
      "url": "/api/v1/admin/lookups/business-areas"
    },
    {
      "key": "risk-statuses",
      "label": "Risk statuses",
      "category": "risk",
      "description": "Core risk workflow states.",
      "itemCount": 6,
      "url": "/api/v1/admin/lookups/risk-statuses"
    }
  ]
}</pre>
                </div>
                <p class="small text-muted">Lookups are grouped by <code>category</code> — e.g. <code>core</code>, <code>risk</code>, <code>action</code>, <code>issue</code>, <code>decision</code>, <code>raid</code>, <code>demand</code>, <code>assumption</code>, <code>dependency</code>, <code>nearmiss</code>, <code>standards</code>, <code>strategy</code>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Get Admin Lookup Items -->
        <div class="api-endpoint">
            <div class="api-endpoint-header">
                <span class="api-method api-method-get">GET</span>
                <span class="api-path">/api/v1/admin/lookups/{key}</span>
                <span class="ml-auto"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
            </div>
            <div class="api-endpoint-body">
                <p>Return every item in a single lookup type, e.g. <code>/api/v1/admin/lookups/risk-statuses</code>.</p>

                <h5 class="mt-3">Path parameters</h5>
                <table class="api-param-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Parameter</th>
                            <th>Type</th>
                            <th>Description</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="api-param-name">key</span> <span class="api-param-required">required</span></td>
                            <td><span class="api-param-type">string</span></td>
                            <td>Kebab-case lookup key as returned by <code>GET /api/v1/admin/lookups</code> (e.g. <code>business-areas</code>, <code>risk-statuses</code>).</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <h5 class="mt-3">Query parameters</h5>
                <table class="api-param-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Parameter</th>
                            <th>Type</th>
                            <th>Description</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="api-param-name">includeInactive</span></td>
                            <td><span class="api-param-type">boolean</span></td>
                            <td>Include items that have been deactivated. Default: <code>false</code>.</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <h5 class="mt-3"><span class="api-response-code api-response-200">200 OK</span></h5>
                <div class="api-code-block">
                    <pre>{
  "key": "risk-statuses",
  "label": "Risk statuses",
  "category": "risk",
  "description": "Core risk workflow states.",
  "includeInactive": false,
  "totalRecords": 6,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "code": "new",
      "name": "New",
      "description": "Risk newly identified, not yet triaged.",
      "sortOrder": 0,
      "isActive": true,
      "extra": null
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "code": "open",
      "name": "Open",
      "description": "Risk being managed.",
      "sortOrder": 10,
      "isActive": true,
      "extra": null
    }
  ]
}</pre>
                </div>
                <p class="small text-muted">Some lookup types include a type-specific <code>extra</code> object — for example <code>risk-likelihoods</code> and <code>risk-impact-levels</code> expose <code>matrixScore</code>, <code>risk-tiers</code> exposes <code>governanceLevel</code> and <code>isProposedTier</code>, <code>departments</code> exposes <code>abbreviation</code> / <code>govukStatus</code> / <code>parentDepartmentId</code>, and <code>priorities</code> / <code>rag-defns</code> expose <code>cssClass</code>.</p>

                <h5 class="mt-3"><span class="api-response-code api-response-404">404 Not Found</span></h5>
                <div class="api-code-block">
                    <pre>{
  "error": {
    "code": "NOT_FOUND",
    "message": "Unknown lookup key 'foo'. Call GET /api/v1/admin/lookups to discover supported keys."
  }
}</pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

